  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Support Nepal Earthquake Relief</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">A devastating 7.8 magnitude earthquake on 25 April 2015 and 7.3 magnitude on 12 May claimed life of around 9,000 people in Nepal and directly affected above 8 million people. Due to the destruction of houses, people were forced to refuge in open space and many lost most of their belongings. Around 24,000 classrooms and other school facilities have been damaged. After conducting immediate relief distribution works, now, ECCA is focusing on recovery, rehabilitation and rebuilding works.</narrative>
  </description>
